      "side": 1,
      "message": "This makes names that overlap with the user-accessible namespace. `var_1` is a totally reasonable name for user code. It also generates invalid GLSL names if the name ends in an underscore: `var_` --\u003e `var__1` makes a double underscore, which some GLSL parsers will actually diagnose and fail on.\n\nThe inliner already has a very similar mangling system, but it also probes the symbol table for names when generating its mangled names so it doesn\u0027t overlap usernames. (It also makes its names in the form `_1_var` since the leading underscore keeps us out of user-space, and strips out double-underscores and double-mangles.) How about we factor out that code to a common location and leverage it here?",
